main event: Two witnesses observed two unidentified objects near Franklin, Texas on September 18, 1965.
interesting points: The objects appeared very distant at first, but then seemed to be traveling at a very high rate of speed.
The objects would fade in and out and appear in three different locations, sometimes simultaneously.
The objects were described as shimmering and appearing to fluctuate in brightness, consistent with the behavior of astronomical objects like stars or planets.
The Air Force sent a letter in November 1966 requesting the observer complete a UFOD Form 164 for further evaluation of the sighting.
The report also mentions large weather balloons in the area, one of which was trailing a long cable, but no reports were received about this phenomenon.
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
